## Technicalities

To be parsed by the script `generate.py`.

Each compliant line shall be a tab-separated
(code point, character, stroke sequence regex) triplet,
where:
  1. the stroke sequence regex shall match `[1-5|()\\]+`, and
  2. the character may be immediately followed by either
     (a) nothing, to indicate that it is dual, or
     (b) a caret (^), to indicate that it is traditional-only, or
     (c) an asterisk (*), to indicate that it is simplified-only.

A character shall NOT be marked traditional-only
if the corresponding simplified character is excluded from the character set
due to lack of font support (see section 'Character set' below).

Non-compliant lines will be ignored.

Sequence regex capture groups should:
  1. number at most 5,
  2. not be nested,
  3. contain pure digits separated by pipes, and
  4. be referred to by a backslash followed by a positive decimal digit.
No attempt at validation is made in `generate.py`.


## Character set

With the exception of U+3007 〇 IDEOGRAPHIC NUMBER ZERO,
all included characters shall be CJK Unified Ideographs (main or extension).

This means that the following shall NOT be included:
- U+2E80 to U+2EFF (CJK Radicals Supplement)
- U+2F00 to U+2FDF (Kangxi Radicals)
- U+31C0 to U+31EF (CJK Strokes)
- U+F900 to U+FAFF (CJK Compatibility Ideographs)
- U+2F800 to U+2FA1F (CJK Compatibility Ideographs Supplement)

Moreover, a character shall NOT be included
unless it is supported by the Noto Sans CJK font on Debian 10
(see <https://packages.debian.org/buster/fonts-noto-cjk>).
This is because Noto Sans CJK support on Debian 10
is strongly correlated with font support on Android.


## Forms

Character forms mostly follow 康熙字典 (Kangxi dictionary),
with much leniency and some exceptions.


## Strokes

Strokes are classified per Conway's memory of Nokia dumbphones:

1  ㇐  畫、提  horizontal; raise
2  ㇑  棟、棟鉤  vertical; vertical-with-hook
3  ㇒  撇  left-slash
4  ㇔  捺、點  right-press; dot
5  ㇖  折、彎  turn; bend

Strokes are ordered very leniently.
